'''
A teacher writes a string of uppercase letters representing candy types; students pick candies in pairs — find how many pairs (same letter) can be formed.

Input Format

single string (uppercase letters).

Constraints

0 ≤ length ≤ 1000.

Output Format

integer — total pairs.

Sample Input 0

AABBCC
Sample Output 0

3
Sample Input 1

AAAA
Sample Output 1

2
'''


st = input().upper()
result=0

for i in set(st):
    result+=st.count(i) // 2
print(result)
